    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular circuit diagram with a capacitor, an inductor, an open switch, a voltmeter, and an ammeter. The open switch is located on the bottom horizontal branch. The capacitor C is located on the left vertical branch so that its positive terminal faces upward and its negative terminal faces downward. The voltmeter V is connected to the left vertical branch by wires above and below the capacitor. The ammeter A is located on the top horizontal branch. The inductor L is located on the right vertical branch.\" src=\"/images/9886d1dce0ef0d2ed8e47005cd53d786.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A charged capacitor, an inductor, an ammeter, and an open switch are connected as shown. The switch is then closed. Which pair of graphs correctly shows the current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I of t\"><math alttext=\"I of t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></math></span></span> measured by the ammeter and the potential difference <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta V of t\"><math alttext=\"delta V of t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Î”</mi><mi>V</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></math></span></span> measured by the voltmeter as functions of time where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t equals 0\"><math alttext=\"t equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span> corresponds to the moment the switch is closed?</p>\n",
